I’m sure Americans are super thrilled that their tax dollars went towards arming the Taliban to the teeth. The level of incompetence from #SleepyJoe,  #KamalaHarris and #AntonyBlinken is truly astounding. #Afghanistan #comeonman #sloppyjoe @tuckercarlsontonight

node.text: It’s good our country is finally out of #Afghanistan but the way it was handled was horrible and embarrassing. I don’t put any of that blame on our military — they are the best in the world. I do place a lot of blame on #JoeBiden. He made this into a crisis with his negligence and sloppiness and it didn’t have to be that way.  13 service members did not need to lose their lives. Even Democrats probably know that #PresidentTrump would have handled it better. Much better. It’s also pretty lame that the #Taliban inherited so much of our weapons and equipment — that right there tells you this whole thing was very ill-planned.

node.title: U.S. General Announces Completion of Withdrawal from Afghanistan

node.text: I want to express my most heartfelt wishes, thoughts and prayers to the families of these brave soldiers who lost their life in #Kabul #Afghanistan a few days ago. Several of them were from my state of California. What makes these deaths difficult for me (and probably you) is that it could have all been avoided if we had real leaders in charge who knew what they were doing. But we don’t have that — we have #JoeBiden and #KamalaHarris. Heartbreaking. #FoxNews

node.title: 13 Brave Heroes Who Lost Their Lives Saving Others in Afghanistan

 #JakeTapper: We are “watching a tragic foreign policy disaster unfold before our eyes...The rapid crumbling of #Afghanistan has caught the #Biden #WhiteHouse flat footed.”

“It seems shocking that President Biden could’ve been so wrong” 

#SleepyJoe #KamalaHarris #Comeonman

node.text: Apparently #HunterBiden suddenly discovered his artistic side, right after his dad became President. Imagine if #DonaldTrumpJr started to sell paintings to unknown individuals for large sums of cash while his dad was #POTUS. I wonder if the media would care. 🤨 Well, since he’s the son of a prominent establishment Democrat, most of the media just shrugs and asks when the art show is. That my friends, is true privilege right there, and if is enjoyed by prominent Democrat politicians and their families. #WheresHunter ? Well, he’s an arTIST now and he’s willing to sell you his art if you can hook him up with some cash or another kushy no-show job he’s not qualified for. Everyone should absolutely demand all of those “Art deals” are 100% transparent, but we know it probably won’t happen. #SleepyJoe will just shrug and deflect it, if he’s even asked, just like he did during the election.  It’s pretty sad that our media is 95% one sided and biased beyond comprehension. Isn’t that how it is in China and North Korea? 🤔 👏🏼 #comeonman #sleepyjoe #cnn #obama #barackobama #democrats

node.text: It’s good our country is finally out of #Afghanistan but the way it was handled was horrible and embarrassing. I don’t put any of that blame on our military — they are the best in the world. I do place a lot of blame on #JoeBiden. He made this into a crisis with his negligence and sloppiness and it didn’t have to be that way.  13 service members did not need to lose their lives. Even Democrats probably know that #PresidentTrump would have handled it better. Much better. It’s also pretty lame that the #Taliban inherited so much of our weapons and equipment — that right there tells you this whole thing was very ill-planned.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Tibbetts, 20, was remembered as a kind and bright young woman who was quick to help others and planned a career in child psychology. Her mother, Laura Calderwood, addressed Bahena Rivera in a victim impact statement read by a representative to the court.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Calderwood recalled being told by tearful investigators that her daughter's body had been found, and racing to inform relatives of the heartbreaking news before they learned what happened from the media. The hardest conversation was with Mollie's grandmother, who was in disbelief that someone "could harm such a beautiful, vibrant young woman so full of promise," she said.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Calderwood recalled being told by tearful investigators that her daughter's body had been found, and racing to inform relatives of the heartbreaking news before they learned what happened from the media. The hardest conversation was with Mollie's grandmother, who was in disbelief that someone "could harm suc such a beautiful, vibrant young woman so full of promise," she said.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Tibbetts vanished on a rural road outside her hometown of Brooklyn, lowa, population 1,700, while while out for one of her near-daily runs on July 18, 2018. Bahena Rivera led investigators to her body a month later. Family members and co-workers feared something was wrong when Tibbetts did not show up for her summer job at a daycare the next morning.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Hundreds of volunteers and law enforcement officers searched for her for weeks but came up empty. Investigators began focusing on Bahena Rivera, who worked under an alias at a nearby dairy farm, after finding a homeowner's surveillance video appearing to show his Chevy Malibu repeatedly driving past Tibbetts while she ran.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'After a lengthy interrogation, Bahena Rivera led authorities to a field where he had buried Tibbetts' body under leaves and stalks. Only her bright running shoes were visible. An autopsy found she had been stabbed several times.'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Bahena Rivera told investigators that he approached Tibbetts because he found her attractive, and that he fought with her after she threatened to call the police. He said he then blacked out and came to as he was driving with her body in his trunk.'.
Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be a closeup of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text: A very confused #JoeBiden: "I'm here, uh, uh, eh, the #FEMA's director's on, uh, uh, FEMA Director Criswell, she's on. And I'm here with, uh, with my senior adviser and a boy who knows #Louisiana very, very well, man, and, and #NewOrleans, Cedric Richmond." 👏🏼 Boy that was tough getting through all those words and names, tell you what. Is it nap time yet, Jack? #comeonman I don’t think he’ll ever know his #FemaDirector’s name. It’s #DeanneCriswell. Remember Joe?  You appointed her?  No?  And all this despite him wearing an ear piece with his aides guiding him through every single word and name. Imagine #SleepyJoe completely on his own. 👀 #hurricaneida

node.text: I guess we’re back to almost going to war with #NorthKorea again. #JoeBiden voters couldn’t stand that we were making real progress with #DPRK under #PresidentTrump. Do you remember when #DonaldTrump made history by meeting with #KimJongUn at the #DMZ and then stepping over to the other side of the border and becoming the first President to do so?  They might have just been good gestures but I’m positive if Trump had 4 more years he would work things out with Kim. Now, with #SleepyJoe in charge, it’s politics as usual which apparently means we’re just too good to talk to our adversaries.  Liberals made fun of Trump’s meetings with Kim but I guess they wanted this crap again, instead. 🤷🏻‍♂️ #comeonman #rocketman

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'North Korea has apparently restarted its Yongbyon nuclear reactor, IAEA says, citing satellite imagery 30 Aug, 2021 01:32 A North Korean nuclear plant in Yongbyon is photographed before a cooling tower was demolished on June 27, 2008 © REUTERS/Kyodo'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'North Korea appears to have restarted its plutonium-producing nuclear reactor at Yongbyon after almost a three-year pause, the UN's nuclear watchdog said in its annual report on the country. Monitoring of the site through satellite imagery showed indications that the 5- megawatt reactor was put back in operation as of early July after apparently being idle since December 2018, the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) said in its report. The agency noted that since last month, there have been discharges of cooling water "consistent with the operation of the reactor."'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'North Korea warns of 'VERY GRAVE SITUATION' for US, says Biden blundered by calling its self-defense efforts 'serious threats''.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'The UN nuclear watchdog pointed out, however, that it "cannot confirm either the operational status" of the facilities listed in the report, nor "nature and purpose of activities conducted therein.' The ΙΑΕΑ heavily elies satellite imagery and so-called "open source information" in its reporting on the reclusive nation. The agency's inspectors were expelled by Pyongyang in 2009. on'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Continuation of the country's nuclear program would be a "clear violation" of UN Security Council resolutions, the IAEA said. "The DPRK's nuclear activities continue to be a cause for serious concern, "the agency added. "Furthermore, the new indications of the operation ot the.. reactor and the radiochemical laboratory are deeply troubling."'.

Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'A steam plant that serves the radiochemical laboratory operated for about five months earlier this year, ending in early July, the ΙΑΕΑ claimed. That timeframe, the agency argued, suggests that reprocessing work to separate plutonium from spent reactor fuel may have been done, rather than the shorter stint that would be needed for maintenance work or waste treatment. Uranium mining work also appears to be active, it said.'.
Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
Photo by 𝕌𝕟𝕗𝕚𝕝𝕥𝕖𝕣𝕖𝕕.ℙ𝕠𝕝𝕚𝕥𝕚𝕔𝕤 on August 29, 2021. May be an image of map, sky and text that says 'Hurricane Katrina August 29th, 2005 Hurricane Ida August 29th, 2021'.
